FBIS3-1263 "drafr057_a_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Burundi Ministers Give Conflicting Reports on Violence LD2403092694 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 GMT 24 Mar 94 LD2403092694 Paris Radio France International Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Tension still prevails in Bujumbura, in Burundi. [passage omitted] The Burundian interior minister told RFI that he attributed the violence that has been going on in the country since last October's aborted coup to undisciplined officers. However, his point of view has been contradicted by the prime minister, whom we also spoke to on the phone this morning.
